Here’s a TekAutomate Steps UI flow for your request, using only real step types and verified SCPI commands for the Tektronix MSO4/5/6 Series via pyvisa backend.

```json
{
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "connect",
      "id": "connect_scope",
      "title": "Connect to Scope"
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "set_ch1_scale",
      "title": "Set CH1 Vertical Scale to 1V/div",
      "params": {
        "command": "CH1:SCAle 1"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "set_ch1_coupling",
      "title": "Set CH1 Coupling to DC",
      "params": {
        "command": "CH1:COUPling DC"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "set_ch1_impedance",
      "title": "Set CH1 Input Impedance to 50 Ohm",
      "params": {
        "command": "CH1:IMPedance 50"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "set_trigger_edge",
      "title": "Set Edge Trigger on CH1, Rising, 0.5V",
      "params": {
        "command": "TRIGger:A:TYPe EDGE;:TRIGger:A:EDGE:SOUrce CH1;:TRIGger:A:EDGE:SLOpe RISing;:TRIGger:A:LEVel:CH1 0.5"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "set_single_acquisition",
      "title": "Set Acquisition Mode to Single",
      "params": {
        "command": "ACQuire:STATE 0;:ACQuire:STOPAfter SEQuence"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "start_acquisition",
      "title": "Start Acquisition",
      "params": {
        "command": "ACQuire:STATE 1"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "error_check",
      "id": "error_check_after_acq",
      "title": "Check for Errors"
    },
    {
      "type": "query",
      "id": "measure_frequency",
      "title": "Measure Frequency on CH1",
      "params": {
        "command": "MEASUrement:MEAS1:TYPe FREQuency;:MEASUrement:MEAS1:SOUrce1 CH1;:MEASUrement:MEAS1:VALue?"
      },
      "resultVar": "frequency"
    },
    {
      "type": "query",
      "id": "measure_amplitude",
      "title": "Measure Amplitude on CH1",
      "params": {
        "command": "MEASUrement:MEAS2:TYPe AMPLitude;:MEASUrement:MEAS2:SOUrce1 CH1;:MEASUrement:MEAS2:VALue?"
      },
      "resultVar": "amplitude"
    },
    {
      "type": "query",
      "id": "measure_pk2pk",
      "title": "Measure Pk2Pk on CH1",
      "params": {
        "command": "MEASUrement:MEAS3:TYPe PK2PK;:MEASUrement:MEAS3:SOUrce1 CH1;:MEASUrement:MEAS3:VALue?"
      },
      "resultVar": "pk2pk"
    },
    {
      "type": "comment",
      "id": "show_results",
      "title": "Show Measurement Results",
      "params": {
        "comment": "Frequency: ${frequency}\nAmplitude: ${amplitude}\nPk2Pk: ${pk2pk}"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "save_waveform",
      "id": "save_waveform_ch1",
      "title": "Save CH1 Waveform",
      "params": {
        "channel": "CH1",
        "filename": "CH1_waveform.csv"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "save_screenshot",
      "id": "save_screenshot",
      "title": "Save Screenshot",
      "params": {
        "filename": "scope_screenshot.png"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "disconnect",
      "id": "disconnect_scope",
      "title": "Disconnect from Scope"
    }
  ]
}
```

This flow:
- Connects to the scope
- Configures CH1 (1V/div, DC, 50Ω)
- Sets edge trigger (rising, 0.5V)
- Runs a single acquisition
- Queries frequency, amplitude, and pk2pk on CH1
- Saves the waveform and a screenshot
- Disconnects

Let me know if you want to adjust filenames or add more steps!

